[slide]
# HTML
## Setup An HTML Page

0. Create a new file called index.html
0. Open that file in your web browser


[slide]
# HTML
## DOCTYPE

The DOCTYPE is used to identify itself to a browser. DOCType is a unique `void` element _(no closing slash)_.

||code html||

<!-- HTML 5 -->
<!DOCTYPE html>

<!-- Other DOCTYPEs -->
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN"
	"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd">

<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC
	"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN"
	"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd">

||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## html

`HTML` is a `normal` element and should wrap all other elements. The DOCTYPE `html` refers to it being the `top-level` element.

||code html||
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	...
</html>
||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## head

`HEAD` is a `normal` element that is not visible to users. It primarily contains special instructions and meta data.

||code html||
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
	<head>
		...
	</head>
</html>
||code||


[slide]
# HTML
## title

`TITLE` is a `normal` element that sets the title of the page. In a web browser, this is what appears in the title bar of the tab or window.

||code html||
<head>
	<title>Hello, World</title>
</head>
||code||


[slide]
# HTML
## meta

`META` tags are void elements with special instructions. 

||code html||
<head>
	<title>Hello, World</title>
	<meta name="..." content="..." />
</head>
||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## meta / `description`

Some `META` tags simply provide more information about the page.

||code html||
<head>
	<title>Hello, World</title>
	<meta name="description"
				content="info about this page" />
</head>
||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## meta / `expires`

Some `META` tags tell the the browser how it should treat a page.

||code html||
<head>
	<title>Hello, World</title>
	<meta name="expires"
				content="Fri, 30 Aug 2013" />
</head>
||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## meta / `robots`

Some `META` tags tell `crawlers` how they should treat a page.

||code html||
<head>
	<title>Hello, World</title>
	<meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
</head>
||code||



[slide]
# HTML
## meta / `refresh`

Some `META` tags tell the the browser something it should do.

||code html||
<head>
	<title>Hello, World</title>
	<meta name="refresh" content="30" />
</head>
||code||



